summary: Genetically engineered immune cells wipe out lupus in mice - Scientists have found that CAR-T therapy, a novel treatment that...
caption: Genetically engineered immune cells wipe out lupus in mice - Scientists have found that CAR-T therapy, a novel treatment that wipes out the immune system’s B cells, cures mice of the condition. It has excited researchers because it is a therapy already approved for people with blood cancer.
